{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nPackage the analyzer + its one pip dependency (lizard) behind an optional `[metrics]` extra, mirroring the existing `grounding`/`agents` extras. scc and jscpd are EXTERNAL CLIs (not pip deps) detected at runtime. Core-only install must import cleanly and degrade code_health to Unavailable.\n\n## Review-driven corrections\n- Register `metrics` in `src/rebar/_optional.EXTRAS` (probe module + install blurb) — the friendly \"install rebar[metrics]\" guidance and `guard_import(extra=\"metrics\")` both require the entry; `guard_import` raises `OptionalDependencyError` (it does not return), so adapters CATCH it and convert to Unavailable.\n- `src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py` is CREATED by blocker 3b30 — this ticket EXTENDS it (adds the guarded lizard import path), it does not create/own it.\n- Respect the import-linter optionality ban-list: `import rebar` / `import rebar.metrics` must stay dependency-free (lizard imported lazily inside the analyzer, never at package import).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `[project.optional-dependencies] metrics = [\"lizard>=1.23\"]` + comment (scc/jscpd = external CLIs); `metrics` added to `_optional.EXTRAS`.\n- [ ] lizard reached via `guard_import(..., extra=\"metrics\")`; missing extra -> `OptionalDependencyError` caught -> Unavailable(reason names the extra), no ImportError escapes, `import rebar[.metrics]` stays dependency-free.\n- [ ] Core-only install: `rebar metrics` does not crash; code_health reports Unavailable.\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Test simulating missing extra -> Unavailable; import-linter/optionality check still green.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30 (interface). Recorded edge: depends_on 3b30.\n## Files likely touched: pyproject.toml, src/rebar/_optional.py, src/rebar/metrics/analyzer.py (extend), tests/unit/metrics/test_metrics_extra_guard.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: S-M"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784523329311191001,"uuid":"92fc4acb-e908-4c27-b8a2-ab4b6c317ee9"}